reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Soft yet effective!
reviews.reviewText: I have always preferred manual toothbrushes that are extra soft, which are not easily available in most markets these days. So I’m very happy these brushes are gentle, and my teeth feel very clean. And each brush comes with a breathable cap to keep other germs at bay. Worth every penny!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 22, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I actually bought these to brush my dogs, teeth, as she has very sensitive gums at her old age of 16. They are almost too soft, but the long handle makes them work.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 19, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Love love love this toothbrush! I had my parents and my sister buy them too. They are so soft and comfortable to brush with.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Better for your teeth and gums
reviews.reviewText: Periodontist recommended "ultra soft" tooth brushes for better cleaning. First time using these I noticed that they were much gentler on my gums than even the "soft" brushes from the major brands. I could tell from feeling my teeth with my tongue that they were smoother after brushing with these. After a couple months, even my dentist noticed that my teeth were cleaner and gums showed less physical trauma from brushing. I think everyone should be using these, and all the manufacturers should be making these in volume, to bring the price down. I think Colgate has their version, but it costs a lot more than their high volume models.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Is this genuine Pectrus?
reviews.reviewText: There are no brand name indications on the brushes. I wonder if these are imitations of the original make?I see a brand called Way-v looking exactly like Pectrus, an obvious copy. When a product is good usually the Chinese come in to copy it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Grrrrreat tooth Brush
reviews.reviewText: I used manual tooth brushes for years. They were hurting my gums badly, to the point I hated to brush my teeth. Then at my last dental visit I was given a new tooth brush. When I used it it was much softer than my regular brushes. So I started looking for soft brushes on Amazon, and reading reviews. I came upon these brushes, and went ahead and placed my order. No sooner than I received them I started using them. Oh the softness of this brush against my teeth and gums was nothing less than transformative. Now I brush 3 or 4 times a day, or whenever I eat anything. I bought these for all members of my family. Happy family here again. Oh BTW, if your current tooth brush is making you hesitate to brush your teeth thoroughly, decay will start and with time you may require teeth implants, at $3000 to $5000 each, check it out at your dentist. Experience talks here.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best toothbrushes ever
reviews.reviewText: I have had issues in the past with gingivitis, and I still have sensitivity. These toothbrushes have been a game changer. Now that I have used these, I cannot go back to the “soft” kind in a normal store. What is considered to be soft in a normal store is still much rougher than these. I have now stock piled these things and plan to use only them going forward. I would highly recommend these to anyone with sensitive gums.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect softness level
reviews.reviewText: I have bought so many toothbrushes that were supposed to be soft, but they always turn out to be medium not soft. It doesn't matter if they claim to be extra soft, super soft etc. I even tried to buy baby toothbrushes, but same thing medium. These are perfect. They don't damage your gums at all. But still get your teeth clean. I would barely scrub with my old toothbrushes at all, so as to save wear on my gums. These will definitely let me brush more often and longer.
